---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CtaSection from '../components/CtaSection.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | HeatherAI" description="Meet Heather Bauer, RD — the bestselling author and registered dietitian whose 20-year coaching practice powers HeatherAI.">

  <!-- ============ HERO ============ -->
  <section class="min-h-[70vh] flex flex-col items-center justify-center text-center px-6 pt-28 pb-20">
    <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-7xl font-bold leading-[1.1] max-w-[800px] tracking-tight">
      The coach behind<br /><em class="not-italic text-accent">the code.</em>
    </h1>
    <p class="text-lg md:text-xl text-white/50 max-w-[560px] leading-relaxed mt-6">
      Heather Bauer, RD, didn't set out to build an AI. She set out to help people change
      how they eat — and spent her career getting really good at it. HeatherAI is what
      happened next.
    </p>

    <!-- Heather's photo -->
    <div class="mt-14 w-full max-w-[540px]">
      <img
        src="/images/heather-bauer.webp"
        alt="Heather Bauer, RD — founder of HeatherAI"
        class="w-full rounded-2xl shadow-[0_30px_60px_-15px_rgba(0,0,0,0.6)] border border-white/[0.06]"
        loading="eager"
      />
      <p class="mt-4 text-[12px] text-white/30 tracking-wide">
        Heather Bauer, RD &middot; Registered Dietitian &middot; Bestselling Author
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ HER STORY ============ -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 md:px-12 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-12 text-center">The Story</h2>

      <div class="space-y-10 text-white/55 text-base leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          <strong class="text-white block mb-1">It started on the field.</strong>
          Heather Bauer was a high school athlete who discovered that what she ate
          directly changed how she performed. That connection — between food and function,
          between what you put in and what you get out — became the foundation of her career.
          She studied dietetics at the University of Wisconsin and never looked back.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong class="text-white block mb-1">She trained in hospitals. Then she went where the clients were.</strong>
          Her early career started at Maimonides Medical Center in New York City, running
          the pre- and post-natal nutrition program. Then she moved to Equinox Fitness Clubs
          as Nutrition Program Director — where she saw firsthand that even the most
          motivated people struggled not because they lacked information, but because life
          kept getting in the way.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong class="text-white block mb-1">So she built her own practice.</strong>
          Heather founded Heather Bauer Nutrition, a nutrition counseling center on Park Avenue, where she
          worked with NYC's top bankers, lawyers, doctors, mothers, athletes, and celebrities.
          Her approach was different: she didn't hand people a meal plan and send them home.
          She coached them through the real moments — the business dinner, the airport,
          the 10pm kitchen raid — one text at a time, every day.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong class="text-white block mb-1">She wrote the book. Literally, two of them.</strong>
          In 2008, she published <em class="not-italic text-white/75">The Wall Street Diet</em>
          — a weight loss plan for high-pressure professionals who don't have time to diet.
          In 2012 came <em class="not-italic text-white/75">Bread Is the Devil</em>,
          which introduced her coaching frameworks to a national audience: the "Diet Devils"
          that sabotage people's goals and the specific counter-strategies she'd developed
          through thousands of client interactions. Both became bestsellers.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong class="text-white block mb-1">The media came calling.</strong>
          Good Morning America. The Today Show. CNN. The View. Ellen. The New York Times.
          The Wall Street Journal. People Magazine. She became a regular on national
          television and a columnist for the Huffington Post. She spoke at Goldman Sachs,
          Estee Lauder, and The 92nd Street Y. She served on the Cooking Light Magazine
          Nutrition Advisory Board.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong class="text-white block mb-1">She's always been an entrepreneur.</strong>
          In 2012, she founded Bestowed — a monthly subscription box of curated healthy
          food products — which she grew and sold to UrthBox in 2018. She's never been
          content to just practice. She's always been looking for ways to scale what she knows.
        </p>

        <p>
          <strong class="text-white block mb-1">5,000 clients later, the question became obvious.</strong>
          Over a million coaching messages. More than 30,000 appointments.
          Heather had built something rare: a dataset of real behavior change, captured at
          a level of detail no one else has. The question was no longer whether her methodology
          worked — it was whether it could reach more than a handful of people at a time.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ HER VOICE ============ -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 md:px-12 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-[800px] mx-auto">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6 text-center">What it's like to work with Heather.</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-white/45 text-center mb-16 max-w-[560px] mx-auto">
        Her philosophy is simple: <em class="not-italic text-white/70">"Live your life, not your diet."</em>
        No deprivation. No guilt. No starting over from scratch.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div class="p-7 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <p class="text-sm text-white/60 leading-relaxed italic mb-4">
            "She helped me lose over 50 lbs and keep it off 12 months later. I felt so strongly about her plan that I referred her to other family members and she has helped them greatly. She definitely has changed my life for the better."
          </p>
          <div class="text-[11px] text-white/35 uppercase tracking-[2px]">Tom F.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-7 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <p class="text-sm text-white/60 leading-relaxed italic mb-4">
            "Over the years Heather has taught me the tricks on how to behave in all situations — work events, dinner parties, cocktail parties, family gatherings. She is my cheerleader and confidant. I have been to other nutritionists but no one has helped me like Heather."
          </p>
          <div class="text-[11px] text-white/35 uppercase tracking-[2px]">Jeffrey L.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-7 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <p class="text-sm text-white/60 leading-relaxed italic mb-4">
            "I was in such a dark place and the weight just kept going up. From my first consultation with Heather I knew I made the right decision. I started July 1st and by September 5th I am down 10 lbs. I have learned how to have a balanced diet including my love for ice cream. Did I mention I didn't exercise once?"
          </p>
          <div class="text-[11px] text-white/35 uppercase tracking-[2px]">Melissa M.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="p-7 bg-bg-surface border border-white/[0.06] rounded-2xl">
          <p class="text-sm text-white/60 leading-relaxed italic mb-4">
            "Heather Bauer helped me get back to my original weight after the birth of my 2nd child. It was such a relief after gaining close to 40 lbs. Heather showed me how to eat smart and not deprive myself."
          </p>
          <div class="text-[11px] text-white/35 uppercase tracking-[2px]">Sydney P.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ WHY HEATHERAI ============ -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 md:px-12 border-t border-white/[0.06]">
    <div class="max-w-[680px] mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-6">Why HeatherAI.</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-white/55 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          The biggest limitation of great coaching has always been access. Heather can
          only work with so many people. The waiting list was long. The price — $950 to
          $3,750 per program — put her out of reach for most.
        </p>

        <p>
          HeatherAI was built to change that. Not to replace Heather — but to take everything
          she's learned across 5,000 clients and make it available to everyone.
          The same coaching methodology. The same behavioral frameworks. The same voice.
          <strong class="text-white/90">Available whenever you need it.</strong>
        </p>

        <p>
          And for those who want the real thing — a private Zoom session with a registered
          dietitian, a personalized plan review, clinical judgment when it matters — the
          <a href="/pricing" class="text-accent hover:underline font-semibold">AI + Human Coach</a>
          plan gives you that too.
        </p>

        <p class="text-base text-white/40">
          Want to understand the data and science behind HeatherAI?
          <a href="/how-it-works" class="text-accent hover:underline">See how it works →</a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <!-- ============ CTA ============ -->
  <CtaSection
    headline={"Experience the coaching Heather built."}
    subline="Start with free meal logging. No credit card required."
    ctaText="Try HeatherAI"
  />

</BaseLayout>
